England Beats India by Six Wickets in Twenty20 Match After Morgan Hits 49

-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   E l s e r
-- 
2011-08-31T20:58:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-31/india-reaches-165-all-out-in-england-twenty20-match-as-rahane-reaches-61.html
England  beat India by six wickets in
their Twenty20 cricket match in Manchester, paced by Eoin Morgan’s 49 runs and Jade Dernbach’s four wickets.  The visitors won the toss and decided to bat, reaching 158-
5 before losing their remaining wickets for seven runs. Dernbach
got Parthiv Patel (10), MS Dhoni (8), Ravichandran Ashwin (4)
and Munaf Patel, who was out without scoring.  Stuart Broad  took
two wickets for England.  England opening batsman Alex Hales was out without scoring
before Morgan combined with  Ravi Bopara  for 73 runs to push the
hosts toward the win. England’s five batsmen other than Hales
all reached double figures with  Kevin Pietersen  hitting 5 fours
on his way to 33. Munaf Patel took two wickets for  India .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at 
 celser@bloomberg.net  